RUSSIAN NAGANT 
CALIBER 7.62X38R
The Nagant M1895 Revolver was a seven-shot, gas-seal revolver designed and produced by Belgian industrialist Léon Nagant for Tsarist Russia. The Nagant M1895 was chambered for a proprietary cartridge, 7.62x38R, and featured an unusual "gas-seal" system in which the cylinder moved forward when the gun was cocked to close the gap between the cylinder and the barrel, providing a (theoretical) boost to the muzzle velocity of the fired projectile. title: RUSSIAN NAGANT REVOLVER
postcontent:
RUSSIAN NAGANT 
CALIBER 7.62X38R
The Nagant M1895 Revolver was a seven-shot, gas-seal revolver designed and produced by Belgian industrialist Léon Nagant for Tsarist Russia. The Nagant M1895 was chambered for a proprietary cartridge, 7.62x38R, and featured an unusual "gas-seal" system in which the cylinder moved forward when the gun was cocked to close the gap between the cylinder and the barrel, providing a boost to the muzzle velocity of the fired projectile. 

* box of 50 rounds included (FIOCCHI)
* ammo sold at any FIOCCHI dealer (7.62 nagant)
* nice holster included

title: DPMS LR-308C .308 20" With 5 mags, scope, mount, and more
postcontent:
This is a DPMS LR-308C "Classic" with the standard 20" barrel.  It is in near PERFECT condition with only a couple hundred rounds through it -- and yes, I followed the recommended break-in procedure (one less thing for you to have to do).  This rifle has always been meticulously cleaned.  It comes with FIVE (5) magazines (all high-cap), two of which are brand new and still in the package, a 3-9x40 scope, a quick-detach one-piece scope mount that removes quickly with no tools for instant use of your backup sights, a vortex flash hider (looks and works great), and an M1 marksman's sling (which can be used to support the rifle in both the loop and hasty sling configurations). 

This is a sub-MOA rifle.  I can shoot 1 MOA from unsupported field positions with this thing!  I can vouch for it being a 1000 yard rifle... it has no trouble dinging the 1000 yard silhouette at Badlands Tactical from prone unsupported.  800 yard shots are child's play with this thing if you know what you're doing.  All this with plain NATO surplus ammo mind you (I mostly shoot British Radway Green 147gr out of it).  It has always been stone cold reliable for me... no op-rod to break like M1As love to do so frequently, and whatever optics you desire are extremely easy to mount with the standard-height flat-top receiver, which is a little longer than those on the poodle shooter caliber ARs.  

This is NOT the super-heavy bull barreled version.  This is NOT a bench queen.  This is NOT the stubby 16" version either (you know, the one that throws a 3-foot muzzle flash from wasting half the powder burned out the muzzle, making the bullet's energy fade away after 600 yards or so and instantly blinding you while giving your position away to anyone within 3 miles)... this is a first-rate Main Battle Rifle.  It compares VERY favorably in accuracy, ergonomics, and price with the M14/M1A, the FAL, the G-3 types, and pretty much any other battle rifle you could think of.  Its a real rifleman's rifle, believe me.  

I think I'm being pretty damn reasonable with the price considering all the stuff that comes with it, especially considering what it would cost YOU to buy one of these plus all the mags and other included stuff, but if you don't like the price, then you can call or e-mail me and try to convince me why it isn't worth that much ;-) .  This thing is in pristine shape.  I'm a marksmanship instructor, so I know how to take care of a rifle.  You will love this thing, I promise... it just feels so right!  ;-)  I kind of hesitate to sell it, actually... I'll buy it back from you if you don't like it.  Hit me up before I change my mind.  I split my time between Stillwater, Norman, and OKC.  I can meet you anywhere reasonably close to any of those towns if you want to look at it.  

Phone:  4o588oo5o6 ; e-mail:  REDACTED.  My name is Daniel.

title: 30-06 - 180 gr PSP - Remington Core-Lokt - 20 Rounds
postcontent:
Manufactured by the legendary Remington Arms Company, this product is brand new, brass-cased, boxer-primed, non-corrosive, and reloadable. It is a staple hunting and target practice ammunition.

The Core-Lokt bullet design is the original controlled-expansion bullet - and one of the most effective ever developed. Its progressively tapered copper jacket is locked to a solid lead core, promoting perfectly controlled expansion and high weight retention for absolutely dependable on-game results. 

The "PSP" or Pointed Soft Point version of the Core-Lokt bullet design features a Spitzer shape profile for improved velocity and flatter trajectory. Bullet cores are mechanically locked in place to provide deep penetration. Jackets designed for progressive, reliable expansion to almost twice the original diameter.
